## Coding Standards

### TypeScript
- Strict mode. No `any`. No `@ts-ignore` without reason.
- `type` over `interface` for component props.
- Explicit return types on server actions and API route handlers.

### React & Next.js
- **Server Components first** — `"use client"` only for state, effects, browser APIs.
- No `getServerSideProps`/`getStaticProps` — App Router patterns only.
- Data fetching: async Server Components or route handlers. No `useEffect` for data.
- `<Link>` always, never `<a>`. `<Image>` always, never `<img>`.
- ISR: `export const revalidate = 300` on pages with CMS content.

### Sanity
- Zero inline GROQ. All queries exported from `sanity/lib/queries.ts`.
- Always `safeFetch` — it returns `null` on missing env vars instead of throwing.
- Field selection must be explicit — never `...` spread entire documents.
- Every public doc type: `slug { current }`, `seo { title, description }`.

### Tailwind v4
- PostCSS plugin mode (`@tailwindcss/postcss`) — not CLI mode.
- Brand colors: `dq-50` through `dq-950` (gold palette). Use `dq-600`/`dq-700` as primary.
- Spacing: use `ms-*`/`me-*` (logical properties) for RTL-safe inline spacing.
- Custom keyframes → `app/globals.css`. Expose in `tailwind.config.ts` `extend.animation`.
- v4 opacity: `bg-black/50` syntax, not `bg-opacity-50`.

### RTL / Urdu
- Root HTML: `lang="ur" dir="rtl"`. Never override without justification.
- `rtl:` prefix for directional overrides.
- Body text: `leading-[1.8]` minimum for Urdu glyph clearance.
- Display headings: `leading-[1.2]` to `leading-[1.35]`.
- Font feature: `calt`, `liga` enabled via globals.css for proper ligatures.

